{
  "texts": [
    "These data revealed that diverse cell states and interactions were induced in the hypertrophic and atrophic conditions after PVE and that therapeutic modulation of cell-cell interactions may be harnessed to enhance desired patient outcomes.",
    "Human liver tissue samples.",
    "Human adult liver tissue samples were obtained from macroscopically \"healthy\" tissue that remained from resected human liver of patients with primary or secondary liver tumors or benign liver diseases with or without pretreatment with PVE.",
    "Participants of this study gave their informed consent that their tissue samples and patient data (sex, age, diagnosis) can be used after pseudonymization for research purposes and publication, according to the ethical guidelines of Leipzig University Hospital (006/17-ek, 21 March 2017, revised and renewed 12 February 2019).",
    "Acquired tissue from portal vein embolized livers included samples of regenerating (R) and embolized (E) tissue whereas tissue samples from benign liver diseases were defined as quiescent healthy controls (H) (Supplementary Data 1)."
  ]
}